  • Method Details

    • getMinHeight

      int getMinHeight()
      Get the minimum height for this ChunkData.

      It is not guaranteed that this method will return the same value as WorldInfo.getMinHeight().

      Setting blocks below this height will do nothing.

      Returns:
      the minimum height

    • getMaxHeight

      int getMaxHeight()
      Get the maximum height for this ChunkData.

      It is not guaranteed that this method will return the same value as WorldInfo.getMaxHeight().

      Setting blocks at or above this height will do nothing.

      Returns:
      the maximum height

    • getBiome

      @NotNull @NotNull Biome getBiome(int x, int y, int z)
      Get the biome at x, y, z within chunk being generated
      Parameters:
      x - the x location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      y - the y location in the chunk from minimum (inclusive) - maxHeight (exclusive)
      z - the z location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      Returns:
      Biome value

    • setBlock

      void setBlock(int x, int y, int z, @NotNull @NotNull Material material)
      Set the block at x,y,z in the chunk data to material. Note: setting blocks outside the chunk's bounds does nothing.
      Parameters:
      x - the x location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      y - the y location in the chunk from minHeight (inclusive) - maxHeight (exclusive)
      z - the z location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      material - the type to set the block to

    • getType

      @NotNull @NotNull Material getType(int x, int y, int z)
      Get the type of the block at x, y, z. Getting blocks outside the chunk's bounds returns air.
      Parameters:
      x - the x location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      y - the y location in the chunk from minHeight (inclusive) - maxHeight (exclusive)
      z - the z location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      Returns:
      the type of the block or Material.AIR if x, y or z are outside the chunk's bounds

      Deprecated.
      use getBlockData(int, int, int)
      Get the type and data of the block at x, y, z. Getting blocks outside the chunk's bounds returns air.
      Parameters:
      x - the x location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      y - the y location in the chunk from minHeight (inclusive) - maxHeight (exclusive)
      z - the z location in the chunk from 0-15 inclusive
      Returns:
      the type and data of the block or the MaterialData for air if x, y or z are outside the chunk's bounds
